WEBVTT

00:00.453 --> 00:01.679
Previously on "The Arrangement"...

00:01.694 --> 00:03.206
I really think we should
do something with this.

00:03.230 --> 00:04.787
That side of yourself is fearless,

00:04.812 --> 00:06.465
and I find that very attractive.

00:06.533 --> 00:09.401
I have to go somehow
convince McPherson not to sell

00:09.470 --> 00:10.954
the story Kyle's been dying to direct.

00:10.978 --> 00:12.137
What if you don't?

00:12.206 --> 00:13.672
But my God! I get
to meet Charlotte Banks!

00:13.696 --> 00:15.166
- Yes!
- And her producing partner

00:15.191 --> 00:16.296
saw me in the play,

00:16.321 --> 00:17.810
and now I'm gonna be reading with her.

00:17.834 --> 00:19.945
- That's amazing.
- My God!

00:20.013 --> 00:22.881
She's getting totally sucked
in and it needs to stop,

00:22.950 --> 00:24.367
and that was the whole
point of the photos.

00:24.391 --> 00:26.368
What? You're the one
who leaked the photos?

00:26.393 --> 00:28.251
Kyle West is really just a product

00:28.276 --> 00:29.921
of the Institute of the Higher Mind.

00:29.990 --> 00:30.990
This is sick, Hope.

00:31.058 --> 00:32.858
I've taken the workshop myself.

00:32.926 --> 00:35.010
- What?
- Terence, this is Shaun.

00:35.035 --> 00:37.135
- Megan's friend.
- Yeah.

00:37.431 --> 00:39.464
How hard did you fight for me?

00:39.533 --> 00:42.104
How hard did you try to make
a different deal with her?

00:42.129 --> 00:43.625
Don't come near me again.

00:50.444 --> 00:52.773
So all the data for
the system goes where?

00:52.798 --> 00:55.078
- Put on some server operated by you?
- Correct.

00:55.103 --> 00:56.939
Okay, and how secure is that?

00:56.984 --> 00:59.024
Well, if you're asking if
our servers can be hacked,

00:59.052 --> 01:00.685
it's virtually impossible.

01:00.754 --> 01:02.320
Virtually?

01:02.389 --> 01:04.022
Look, I'll be honest with you.

01:04.090 --> 01:06.791
We can give you the best
security system in the world,

01:06.860 --> 01:10.529
and we will, but if
someone is just hell-bent

01:10.597 --> 01:12.497
on getting past it to
invade your privacy,

01:12.566 --> 01:13.698
they'll find a way.

01:13.767 --> 01:15.467
What are we doing this for?

01:15.536 --> 01:17.335
It's a very effective deterrent.

01:17.404 --> 01:20.253
How many stalkers
have you had, Mr. West?

01:20.941 --> 01:22.774
Three... ish.

01:22.843 --> 01:24.242
You need to do something.

01:24.311 --> 01:26.444
Hey, how's it going?

01:26.513 --> 01:28.013
Quinn was just,

01:28.081 --> 01:29.738
walking me through how
this whole thing works.

01:29.762 --> 01:31.349
It's crazy that somebody got in here.

01:31.418 --> 01:32.984
It's really disturbing.

01:33.053 --> 01:34.986
Well, we're installing
motion-detector lights,

01:35.055 --> 01:37.188
there's sensors on
the doors and windows,

01:37.257 --> 01:38.735
and we've got internal-external cameras,

01:38.759 --> 01:39.824
carbon monoxide alarms...

01:39.893 --> 01:41.359
Security cameras inside the house?

01:41.428 --> 01:42.839
Well, if there's a
break-in, you want to know

01:42.863 --> 01:44.262
exactly where the intruder is.

01:44.331 --> 01:46.466
Right, but isn't the point
of all this other stuff

01:46.491 --> 01:48.567
to prevent the break-ins
in the first place?

01:48.635 --> 01:51.870
Sorry, obviously, I want
to do everything we can.

01:51.939 --> 01:54.506
It's just the idea of
cameras makes me feel like

01:54.575 --> 01:57.173
I'm gonna end up on
a sex tape somewhere.

01:58.612 --> 02:00.545
No interior cameras.

02:01.982 --> 02:03.882
Okay.

02:03.951 --> 02:05.383
Thank you.

02:07.254 --> 02:09.167
Okay, I'm off to set.

02:09.356 --> 02:12.208
Zach told me that he's the only
one who checked her references.

02:12.240 --> 02:14.256
This doesn't make you nervous?

02:14.294 --> 02:16.161
It seems to make you nervous.

02:16.229 --> 02:19.097
Okay, what is going on with you?

02:19.166 --> 02:21.333
Kyle's house was broken into.

02:21.401 --> 02:23.068
Now there's some woman
that we don't know

02:23.136 --> 02:24.533
installing a new security system?

02:24.558 --> 02:26.037
Why are you not all over this?

02:26.106 --> 02:27.684
Kyle and I made a
mutual decision to take

02:27.708 --> 02:29.240
a step back from each other.

02:29.309 --> 02:31.719
Okay, what happened? Tell me.

02:32.245 --> 02:34.679
So you can distance
yourself from the fray?

02:34.748 --> 02:36.320
No.

02:36.345 --> 02:39.584
So I can navigate what I'm
sure is an emotional minefield.

02:39.653 --> 02:42.287
He's been wanting independence.
I'm respecting that.

02:42.356 --> 02:43.555
What else happened?

02:43.624 --> 02:46.448
The rest is between him and me.

02:46.827 --> 02:49.661
Look, my job is a lot easier
when he has a clear head,

02:49.730 --> 02:52.063
and this lovers' quarrel
that's between the two of you

02:52.132 --> 02:53.531
does not help me right now.

02:53.600 --> 02:55.876
Well, I'm sorry about that.

02:57.170 --> 03:00.872
Does this conscious uncoupling
extend to the Institute as well?

03:00.941 --> 03:03.241
Look, DeAnn, the sky
is not falling, okay?

03:03.310 --> 03:05.243
I've got plenty of things to catch up on

03:05.312 --> 03:07.846
until Kyle finds his
way back, which he will

03:07.914 --> 03:11.740
as soon as he realizes that he
is not built to do this alone.

